\begin_layout Section*
Technical Description
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Each Superbot module consists of two linked cubes with two end effectors,
 allowing three degrees of rotational freedom (270º of roll, and 180º each
 of pitch and yaw), making them extremely flexible.
 Each module weighs 500 grams, and is 16.8cm long when fully extended.
 Each module has its own ATMegal128 microcontroller, a 3D accelerometer/inclinom
eter, power source, and actuators, making it fully capable of independent
 action.
 Six genderless universal connectors (found on each side of the end effectors)
 allow connection and communication between modules, enabling a collection
 of Superbots to act as a single robot.
 In this case, the collection is governed by ID-free distributed software
 loaded on each of the modules, and there is no central executive 
